Develop a basic poll application (app).It should consist of two parts: 
        a)  A public site in which user can pick their favourite programming language and vote. 
        b)  An admin site that lets you add, change and delete programming languages.

Create a Django Project and App:
Create a Django project and an app within the project:

django-admin startproject poll_project
cd poll_project
python manage.py startapp poll_app


Define Models:
Open the models.py file in the poll_app directory and define the models for programming languages and votes.

# poll_app/models.py
from django.db import models

class Language(models.Model):
    name = models.CharField(max_length=50)

class Vote(models.Model):
    language = models.ForeignKey(Language, on_delete=models.CASCADE)
    ip_address = models.GenericIPAddressField()

Apply Migrations:
Run the following commands to apply migrations and create the database tables:

python manage.py makemigrations
python manage.py migrate

Create Views:
Open the views.py file in the poll_app directory and define views for the public site and admin site.

# poll_app/views.py
from django.shortcuts import render, redirect
from .models import Language, Vote

def index(request):
    languages = Language.objects.all()
    return render(request, 'poll_app/index.html', {'languages': languages})

def admin(request):
    languages = Language.objects.all()
    return render(request, 'poll_app/admin.html', {'languages': languages})

Create URLs:
Define URLs in the urls.py file in the poll_app directory.

# poll_app/urls.py
from django.urls import path
from .views import index, admin

urlpatterns = [
    path('', index, name='index'),
    path('admin/', admin, name='admin'),
]

Include these URLs in the project's urls.py.

# poll_project/urls.py
from django.contrib import admin
from django.urls import include, path

urlpatterns = [
    path('admin/', admin.site.urls),
    path('', include('poll_app.urls')),
]

Create Templates:
Create HTML templates for the public site (index.html) and admin site (admin.html) in the poll_app/templates/poll_app directory.

poll_app/templates/poll_app/index.html:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Programming Language Poll</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Vote for Your Favorite Programming Language</h1>
    <form action="{% url 'index' %}" method="post">
        {% csrf_token %}
        {% for language in languages %}
            <label>
                <input type="radio" name="language" value="{{ language.id }}">
                {{ language.name }}
            </label><br>
        {% endfor %}
        <button type="submit">Vote</button>
    </form>
</body>
</html>

poll_app/templates/poll_app/admin.html:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Admin - Programming Language Poll</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Admin - Manage Programming Languages</h1>
    <ul>
        {% for language in languages %}
            <li>{{ language.name }} - Votes: {{ language.vote_set.count }}</li>
        {% endfor %}
    </ul>
</body>
</html>

Run the Development Server:
Run the development server with the following command:
python manage.py runserver
